{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"af99e831-d72c-48b4-bd7c-12dc25ade37f","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote: xUnit embeds the skip reason in `[Fact]`/`[Theory]` directly — there's no separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1732648b-ceb6-45f4-add7-09a2d4a38396","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":308,"requestId":"67C0:1E3875:2AAAB73:2F27000:69FD3A13"},"id":"2fc4b310-b6f9-411a-bf48-969d42634be8","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:19:21.429Z","parentId":"59e22300-1e53-4ea1-ae68-7e3505767be5"}
